description.narrative: By 2022, caregivers, family members, communities and institutions, particularly in the four most deprived states/regions, have increased knowledge and skills to practice appropriate child care, hygiene, feeding, dietary, early stimulation, injury and violence prevention during critical periods of growth and development and to demand quality health and nutrition services, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Evaluation And Research, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more children under 5 and women of reproductive age equitably access and utilize evidence-based health, HIV & nutrition interventions, including adoption of key behaviours, especially among vulnerable populations in most deprived states/regions, conflict-affected and peri-urban areas (Goal Area 1 UNICEF Strategic Framework 2018-2021)

description.narrative: UNICEF's supported Myanmar's government COVID-19 response in reaching an estimated 38 million people with COVID-19 related preventative messages. The risk communication and community engagement were expanded to support immediate resumption of essential maternal, newborn, child health services especially routine immunization. UNICEF supported Department of Public Health, Ministry of Health and Sports on the nation-wide introduction of Rota Virus Vaccine in February; Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE) activities for COVID-19 prevention at national, institutional and community levels; resumption of routine immunization services and building partnership with civil society organization on-demand generation for immunization services in urban and peri-urban areas. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/07/2020
